import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='values', bins=30, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['values'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['values'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of values?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Values")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='values', data=data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    average_values_count = data['values_count'].mean()
    ax = sns.barplot(x='date', y='values_count', data=data)
    ax.axhline(average_values_count, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {average_values_count:.2f}')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the average count of values?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns

    return plt;
